	<div id="p59535" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p59535"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />by <strong>Polter</strong> &raquo; Thu Jul 29, 2004 4:25 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Yeah those NPCs in DSP are just plain fun. You get a taste of just how powerful charm can be at 39. FYI for others reading who are not familiar - these NPCs are lvl 45 so they are red. However they are not incredibly resistant and you can still charm them somewhat reliably. 
<br />
<br />There is also an NPC camp quite close to the NL zoneline. The gnome inside the tent can easily be single pulled without Pacify or anything. Give him a couple weapons and he'll quad for 178 and has a TON of HP like the rest of em. I did 39 to 41 here and then I actually went back to the basilisks in Surefall till 43.
<br />
<br />The hopper caves are camped 24/7 on my server, and even so the idea of a 60% hasted whacko that wants my head coming after me in the caves just doesn't appeal to me hehe. I'm currently in the Dreadlands and find that the drolvarg ragers make good pets. I can usually get 6 to 8 kills before I have to put my pet down. XP is still pretty good. I get 20% about every 30 to 40 minutes. As an aside for anyone thinking about going the Dreadlands route, don't bother charming the ravishing drolvargs. Yeah they have a ton of HP and hit for 110ish, but they break charm way too often to make it worth it.
<br />
<br />I'm currently lvl 47 with 3 days and 11 hours /played. I &lt;3 Charm  :lol: 
<br />
<br />Polter</div>

			

		</div>

		
